## Database (MongoDB)

- Schema-first: always define Mongoose schema or Prisma model before writing service logic
- `_id`: use default ObjectId unless there's a specific reason for custom IDs
- Field names: `camelCase` in documents (MongoDB convention)
- Indexes: define explicitly in schema (`index: true` or dedicated `createIndexes()`)
- Transactions: use sessions for multi-document operations
- Never store sensitive data (passwords, tokens) in plain text
- Migrations: use a migration tool (migrate-mongo or Prisma migrate) — never modify collections manually in production
